{#- Hands the caller to a Telnyx AI Assistant ON THE SAME call leg.

    BILLING (why this isn't <Dial>): <Connect><AIAssistant> attaches the assistant
    to the existing inbound leg. It does NOT originate a new outbound <Dial> leg,
    so there is no second concurrent telephony leg and no $0.10-per-invocation
    transfer fee. Only the AI minute (~$0.05/min) stacks on the one inbound leg.
    Never reach the assistant via <Dial> to a number — that would run two metered
    legs at once ("charged twice") plus the transfer fee.

    The assistant's voice, greeting, instructions, and its own transfer-to-human
    tool live on the AI Assistant resource (portal / AI Assistant API) and are
    referenced here only by id — keep that config out of this XML.

    Variables: assistant_id, voice, intro_audio_url (optional), intro_text. -#}
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Response>
{%- if intro_audio_url %}
  <Play>{{ intro_audio_url }}</Play>
{%- elif intro_text %}
  <Say voice="{{ voice }}">{{ intro_text }}</Say>
{%- endif %}
  <Connect>
    <AIAssistant id="{{ assistant_id }}"/>
  </Connect>
</Response>
